00:10:00.820 --> 00:10:01.290
DEREK SLATER: It
was pretty good.

00:10:01.290 --> 00:10:02.460
TIMOTHY JORDAN: But I know
you can tie it together

00:10:02.460 --> 00:10:03.585
for us-- put a bow on this.

00:10:03.585 --> 00:10:05.150
What is a patent troll?

00:10:05.150 --> 00:10:06.120
DEREK SLATER: Yes, so
they were pretty close.

00:10:06.120 --> 00:10:08.280
Patents are supposed to
encourage innovation.

00:10:08.280 --> 00:10:11.246
What patent trolls do is
they don't invent anything.

00:10:11.246 --> 00:10:12.620
They come up with
some broad idea

00:10:12.620 --> 00:10:13.870
that they get a patent
for, and then they

00:10:13.870 --> 00:10:15.270
go around threatening
to sue people.

00:10:15.270 --> 00:10:17.436
Let me tell you a little
story to make that clearer.

00:10:17.436 --> 00:10:20.450
This guy David Bloom was working
at a Fortune 500 company,

00:10:20.450 --> 00:10:22.040
leaves to become
an app developer,

00:10:22.040 --> 00:10:25.120
to start a company called
Ordrx, where restaurants

00:10:25.120 --> 00:10:26.960
can share their menus,
make it easy to be

00:10:26.960 --> 00:10:28.810
ordered from any app.

00:10:28.810 --> 00:10:31.730
Raises millions of dollars in
VC funding, has 20 employees,

00:10:31.730 --> 00:10:32.870
is going along great.

00:10:32.870 --> 00:10:34.870
And then this patent troll
comes along who says,

00:10:34.870 --> 00:10:36.720
I am the inventor.

00:10:36.720 --> 00:10:41.340
I own a patent on sharing
menus, and he sues David Bloom.

00:10:41.340 --> 00:10:43.700
David Bloom tries to
fight it, but he loses

00:10:43.700 --> 00:10:44.977
clients, who get scared off.

00:10:44.977 --> 00:10:46.560
He loses investors
who get scared off.

00:10:46.560 --> 00:10:49.420
And earlier this year had
to go out of business.

00:10:49.420 --> 00:10:53.085
That's a story unfortunately
of too many app developers

00:10:53.085 --> 00:10:53.960
and small businesses.

00:10:53.960 --> 00:10:57.580
It can cost like $1 million
at least to defend yourself,

00:10:57.580 --> 00:11:00.420
and it's happened to people
who create podcasts, like Marc

00:11:00.420 --> 00:11:01.500
Maron and Adam Carolla.

00:11:01.500 --> 00:11:03.790
It's happened to people who
do online test software.

00:11:03.790 --> 00:11:05.960
It's happened to people
just running Wi-Fi routers.

00:11:05.960 --> 00:11:09.490
Last year there were nearly
3,000 patent troll lawsuits.

00:11:09.490 --> 00:11:11.557
That's up 500% over
the last decade.

00:11:11.557 --> 00:11:12.640
This is a growing problem.

00:11:12.640 --> 00:11:15.010
There are more people like
David Bloom every year.

00:11:15.010 --> 00:11:16.260
TIMOTHY JORDAN: This is crazy.

00:11:16.260 --> 00:11:18.640
They're able to get away with
this time and time again.

00:11:18.640 --> 00:11:22.620
Obviously, there's a growing
industry of patent trolls.

00:11:22.620 --> 00:11:23.799
What can we do to fix this?

00:11:23.799 --> 00:11:25.840
DEREK SLATER: So we need
a better system in place

00:11:25.840 --> 00:11:28.331
for having quality
patents to be issued.

00:11:28.331 --> 00:11:30.330
There needs to be deterrence
built in the system

00:11:30.330 --> 00:11:32.300
so that there's some
penalty if you go and file

00:11:32.300 --> 00:11:35.081
one of these frivolous lawsuits
using one of these bad patents.

00:11:35.081 --> 00:11:36.330
TIMOTHY JORDAN: OK, what else?

00:11:36.330 --> 00:11:39.170
DEREK SLATER: The main
thing that people can do

00:11:39.170 --> 00:11:41.280
is they can go and tell
Congress to fix it.

00:11:41.280 --> 00:11:42.740
That's really where the
fix needs to happen.

00:11:42.740 --> 00:11:44.240
Fortunately, in the
House and the Senate

00:11:44.240 --> 00:11:46.281
there are two bills right
now, the Innovation Act

00:11:46.281 --> 00:11:47.530
and the Patent Act.

00:11:47.530 --> 00:11:49.620
If you go to fixpatents.org,
you can go and tell

00:11:49.620 --> 00:11:52.240
your Congress person, your
senator to go and pass those,

00:11:52.240 --> 00:11:53.740
and hopefully that
will happen soon.

00:11:53.740 --> 00:11:56.620
Those bills, among other
things, would make it

00:11:56.620 --> 00:11:59.350
so that if a patent troll
files a lawsuit and they lose,

00:11:59.350 --> 00:12:01.540
they have to pay the other
side's attorneys fees.

00:12:01.540 --> 00:12:03.248
That would be a good
amount of deterrence

00:12:03.248 --> 00:12:05.438
from just going after and
threatening random people.

00:12:05.438 --> 00:12:06.813
TIMOTHY JORDAN:
All right-- 500%?

00:12:06.813 --> 00:12:09.674
DEREK SLATER: 500%, and
over the last 20 years,

00:12:09.674 --> 00:12:11.590
that's about a half
trillion dollars of damage

00:12:11.590 --> 00:12:12.710
to the US economy.

00:12:12.710 --> 00:12:15.122
Last five years, about
$8 billion in lost VC

00:12:15.122 --> 00:12:16.330
funding due to patent trolls.

00:12:16.330 --> 00:12:17.650
TIMOTHY JORDAN: All right
so go to this website.

00:12:17.650 --> 00:12:19.040
DEREK SLATER: Fixpatents.org.

